Egypt Sets $3.4 Billion Power Budget Next Fiscal Year

-- B y   O l a   G a l a l
-- 
2011-04-05T09:30:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/egypt-sets-3-4-billion-power-budget-next-fiscal-year-correct-.html
(Corrects start of fiscal year in first paragraph.)  Egypt ’s power budget for the fiscal
year that starts in July is 20 billion Egyptian pounds ($3.4
billion), Electricity and Energy Minister Hassan Younes said in
a statement today on the ministry’s  website .  The ministry will add 1,500 megawatts of power to meet
rising demand, especially in summer, and the country’s first
solar power plant, with capacity of 140 megawatts, will start
test operations in two weeks, Younes said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ola Galal at 
 ogalal@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Stephen Voss  on   sev@bloomberg.net . 